: "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://www.joes.net/"}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Event", "item": "https://www.joes.net/?post_type=event-custom"}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Sips &#038; Tips: Olivier Leflaive"}]}, {"@type": "WebSite", "@id": "https://www.joes.net/#website", "url": "https://www.joes.net/", "name": "Joe&#039;s Seafood, Prime Steak &amp; Stone Crab", "description": "", "potentialAction": [{"@type": "SearchAction", "target": {"@type": "EntryPoint", "urlTemplate": "https://www.joes.net/?s={search_term_string}"}, "query-input": "required name=search_term_string"}], "inLanguage": "en-US"}], "body_text": "to Continue Our November Somm Series will feature two selections from a world-renowned producer, Olivier Leflaive. Join us November 13-19 for a glass that\u2019s perfect for the season. Olivier Leflaive has been a key figure in Burgundy for nearly five decades, and the wines they produce have always been best in class. Managing every production aspect from the vineyard to the cellar, Leflaive delivers the best wine in Burgundy time and again. The  2020 Olivier Leflaive, Puligny-Montrachet, Burgundy, France ($42 per 6oz / $168 per bottle)  comes from one of the most heralded regions for Chardonnay production in all of Burgundy, Puligny-Montrachet. Noted for its distinct notes of citrus and fresh minerality, this wine is an incredible match for chilled King Crab with drawn butter. \u00a0 \u00a0 The Pinot Noir grapes for the  2017 Olivier Leflaive, P\u00e9zerolles, Pommard, Burgundy, France ($45 per 6oz / $180 per bottle)  comes from an elevated site with iron rich soil on the eastern slope of Pommard. This Premier Cru site contributes an increased depth of color with aromas of violet, sage and menthol. The palate is full of finesse and elegance, covering the palate with fresh red fruit and a firm tannin finish, making a wonderful pairing for our Ahi Tuna Filet. \u00a0 \u00a0 Wine Tip:  The delicate flavors of Burgundy wines are best enjoyed in their own signature Burgundy wine glass. With a medium-wide bowl and a tapered lip, these glasses allow for optimal aeration and enjoyment. To make a reservation, use the widget below or call  Joe's Washington, D.C. at  202-489-0140 .\n\t\t\t Valet Parking Available or  Book with Spothero Sunday 11:30AM - 9:00PM Monday - Saturday 11:30AM - 10:00PM We use cookies to provide the best experience on our website. By continuing to use our site you agree to  our updated privacy policy . for every $100 in gift cards you buy No holiday meal\u00a0is complete without a delicious pie from Joe's. Orders must be placed by Sunday, November 19 for pickup on Tuesday, November 21 or Wednesday, November 22.", "size": 42197, "depth": 3, "download_timeout": 180.0, "download_slot": "www.joes.net", "download_latency": 0.8990869522094727, "status": 200, "links_url": "https://www.joes.net/whats-crackin/sips-tips-olivier-leflaive-2/#main@@https://www.joes.net/chicago/@@https://www.joes.net/las-vegas/@@https://www.joes.net/dc/@@https://www.joes.net@@https://www.joes.net/dc@@https://www.joes.net/dc/reservations/@@https://www.joes.net/dc/menu/@@https://www.joes.net/dc/private-parties/@@https://www.joes.net/dc/carry-out-delivery/@@https://www.joes.net/dc/whats-crackin/@@https://joes.cashstar.com/@@https://tinyurl.com/y9sk3cqh@@https://spothero.app.link/ts1p2NqSe1?kind=destination&id=84048&$3p=a_hasoffers&$affiliate_json=http%3A%2F%2Ftracking.spothero.com%2Faff_c%3Foffer_id%3D1%26aff_id%3D1568%26source%3Djoesseafooddc%26format%3Djson@@https://tinyurl.com/y9sk3cqh@@https://www.joes.net/dc/newsletter-mobile-club@@https://www.joes.net/dc/contact@@https://www.facebook.com/joesstonedc/@@https://twitter.com/Joes_DC@@https://www.instagram.com/joesseafood/@@https://www.lettuce.com@@https://joes.cashstar.com@@https://harri.com/LEYE?filters=brands%253D4489669%25252C4489662%25252C4489657@@https://www.lettuce.com/accessibility/@@https://www.lettuce.com/privacy-